this should be what we override, now where, we need to understand how the exit function works,
the exit function is a libc function, this mean is not in our code, rather is a standard function
what this meant is, the code to make the exit function is somewhere else already in the pc
so any program can acess to this code, and run it. but in memory this is loaded randomly, the libc gets loaded, the code to execute the exit gets loaded but we dont know where, either the program, so the program do a interesting stuff, for any linked function it writes a plt and a GOT, the plt is the function pointer where it will search in the GOT, is called procedure linked table, is like saying we got a document with all the correspondent mail boxes and is telling us which mail box correspond to each person in this case the mail box for the exit function, something like this 
[i][name][mail box number]
[0][samu][10]
[1][andy][99]
[2][cony][77]

we  cannot change the index, where we find our name and our correspondent mailbox number, but we can change the mailbox number, this one must be writable, otherwise even the mannager, the dynamic linker, woulnt assing maibox numbers, so we got to think like this

[PLT][func][GOT]
[0  ][samu][10 ]
[1  ][andy][99 ]
[2  ][cony][77 ]

